Package nonComparisonBasedSortingAlgorithms

Non-Comparison-Based Sorting Algorithms In Java.

This package contains:

Counting Sorting Algorithm. Pigeon-Hole Sorting Algorithm. Radix Sorting Algorithm. Bucket Sorting Algorithm. AmericanFlag Sorting Algorithm. Bead Sorting Algorithm.
Since:
1.0
Version:
1.0
Author:
Rawad Alaryan
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AmericanFlagSortingAlgorithm<T extends Comparable<T>>
    AMERICAN FLAG SORTING ALGORITHM: American Flag Sort is an efficient, In-place variant of Radix Sort.
    BeadSortingAlgorithm<T extends Comparable<T>>
    BEAD SORTING ALGORITHM: Bead Sort is also called "Gravity Sort".
    BucketSortingAlgorithm<T extends Comparable<T>>
    BUCKET SORTING ALGORITHM: Bucket Sort is a Non-Comparison-Based Sorting Algorithm.
    CountingSortingAlgorithm<T extends Comparable<T>>
    COUNTING SORTING ALGORITHM: It is an Integer Sorting Algorithm: We assume the values to be integers.
    PigeonHoleSortingAlgorithm<T extends Comparable<T>>
    PIGEONHOLE SORTING ALGORITHM: Pigeonhole Sorting is a sorting algorithm that is suitable for sorting lists of elements where: The number of elements (n) and the length of the range of possible key values (N) are approximately the same.
    RadixSortingAlgorithm<T extends Comparable<T>>
    RADIX SORTING ALGORITHM: It is a Non-Comparison-Based Sorting Algorithm.
